.TH framework_tool 1  "framework_tool 0.6.5" 
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SH NAME
framework_tool \- Swiss army knife for Framework laptops
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBframework_tool\fR [\fB\-\-flash\-gpu\-descriptor\fR] [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR]... [\fB\-q\fR|\fB\-\-quiet\fR]... [\fB\-\-versions\fR] [\fB\-\-version\fR] [\fB\-\-features\fR] [\fB\-\-esrt\fR] [\fB\-\-device\fR] [\fB\-\-compare\-version\fR] [\fB\-\-power\fR] [\fB\-\-smartbattery\fR] [\fB\-\-smartbattery\-auth\fR] [\fB\-\-thermal\fR] [\fB\-\-sensors\fR] [\fB\-\-fansetduty\fR] [\fB\-\-fansetrpm\fR] [\fB\-\-autofanctrl\fR] [\fB\-\-pdports\fR] [\fB\-\-pdports\-chromebook\fR] [\fB\-\-info\fR] [\fB\-\-meinfo\fR] [\fB\-\-pd\-info\fR] [\fB\-\-pd\-reset\fR] [\fB\-\-pd\-disable\fR] [\fB\-\-pd\-enable\fR] [\fB\-\-dp\-hdmi\-info\fR] [\fB\-\-dp\-hdmi\-update\fR] [\fB\-\-audio\-card\-info\fR] [\fB\-\-privacy\fR] [\fB\-\-pd\-bin\fR] [\fB\-\-ec\-bin\fR] [\fB\-\-capsule\fR] [\fB\-\-dump\fR] [\fB\-\-h2o\-capsule\fR] [\fB\-\-dump\-ec\-flash\fR] [\fB\-\-flash\-full\-ec\fR] [\fB\-\-flash\-ec\fR] [\fB\-\-flash\-ro\-ec\fR] [\fB\-\-flash\-rw\-ec\fR] [\fB\-\-intrusion\fR] [\fB\-\-inputdeck\fR] [\fB\-\-inputdeck\-mode\fR] [\fB\-\-expansion\-bay\fR] [\fB\-\-charge\-limit\fR] [\fB\-\-charge\-current\-limit\fR] [\fB\-\-charge\-rate\-limit\fR] [\fB\-\-get\-gpio\fR] [\fB\-\-fp\-led\-level\fR] [\fB\-\-fp\-brightness\fR] [\fB\-\-kblight\fR] [\fB\-\-remap\-key\fR] [\fB\-\-rgbkbd\fR] [\fB\-\-tablet\-mode\fR] [\fB\-\-touchscreen\-enable\fR] [\fB\-\-haptic\-intensity\fR] [\fB\-\-click\-force\fR] [\fB\-\-stylus\-battery\fR] [\fB\-\-console\fR] [\fB\-\-reboot\-ec\fR] [\fB\-\-ec\-hib\-delay\fR] [\fB\-\-sysinfo\fR] [\fB\-\-uptimeinfo\fR] [\fB\-\-s0ix\-counter\fR] [\fB\-\-hello\fR] [\fB\-\-hash\fR] [\fB\-\-driver\fR] [\fB\-\-pd\-addrs\fR] [\fB\-\-pd\-ports\fR] [\fB\-t\fR|\fB\-\-test\fR] [\fB\-\-test\-retimer\fR] [\fB\-\-boardid\fR] [\fB\-f\fR|\fB\-\-force\fR] [\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR] [\fB\-\-flash\-gpu\-descriptor\-file\fR] [\fB\-\-dump\-gpu\-descriptor\-file\fR] [\fB\-\-validate\-gpu\-descriptor\-file\fR] [\fB\-\-nvidia\fR] [\fB\-\-host\-command\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SH DESCRIPTION
framework_tool is a command\-line utility for interacting with Framework Computer laptops and desktops.
.PP
It communicates with the Embedded Controller (EC) to query firmware versions, battery and USB\-C status, thermal data, privacy and intrusion switches, and expansion card details. It can also adjust system settings and flash EC firmware.
.PP
Most operations require root privileges.
.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-flash\-gpu\-descriptor\fR

.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Increase logging verbosity
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Decrease logging verbosity
.TP
\fB\-\-versions\fR
List current firmware versions
.TP
\fB\-\-version\fR
Show tool version information (Add \-vv for more details)
.TP
\fB\-\-features\fR
Show features support by the firmware
.TP
\fB\-\-esrt\fR
Display the UEFI ESRT table
.TP
\fB\-\-device\fR \fI<DEVICE>\fR
Device type to compare the \-\-compare\-version string against
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
bios
.IP \(bu 2
ec
.IP \(bu 2
pd0
.IP \(bu 2
pd1
.IP \(bu 2
rtm01
.IP \(bu 2
rtm23
.IP \(bu 2
ac\-left
.IP \(bu 2
ac\-right
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-compare\-version\fR \fI<COMPARE_VERSION>\fR
Version to compare device firmware version with
.TP
\fB\-\-power\fR
Show current power status of battery and AC (Add \-vv for more details)
.TP
\fB\-\-smartbattery\fR [\fI<FILE>\fR]
Show detailed smart battery information, or load from dump file
.TP
\fB\-\-smartbattery\-auth\fR
Authenticate smart battery (requires unseal and auth keys)
.TP
\fB\-\-thermal\fR
Print thermal information (Temperatures and Fan speed)
.TP
\fB\-\-sensors\fR
Print sensor information (ALS, G\-Sensor)
.TP
\fB\-\-fansetduty\fR [\fI<FANSETDUTY>...\fR]
Set fan duty cycle (0\-100%)
.TP
\fB\-\-fansetrpm\fR [\fI<FANSETRPM>...\fR]
Set fan RPM (limited by EC fan table max RPM)
.TP
\fB\-\-autofanctrl\fR [\fI<AUTOFANCTRL>\fR]
Turn on automatic fan speed control
.TP
\fB\-\-pdports\fR
Show USB\-C PD port state
.TP
\fB\-\-pdports\-chromebook\fR
Show PD port info (generic Chromium EC)
.TP
\fB\-\-info\fR
Show info from SMBIOS (Only on UEFI)
.TP
\fB\-\-meinfo\fR [\fI<MEINFO>\fR]
Show Intel ME information (from SMBIOS type 0xDB). Optionally provide a dmidecode binary dump file path
.TP
\fB\-\-pd\-info\fR
Show details about the PD controllers
.TP
\fB\-\-pd\-reset\fR \fI<PD_RESET>\fR
Reset a specific PD controller (for debugging only)
.TP
\fB\-\-pd\-disable\fR \fI<PD_DISABLE>\fR
Disable all ports on a specific PD controller (for debugging only)
.TP
\fB\-\-pd\-enable\fR \fI<PD_ENABLE>\fR
Enable all ports on a specific PD controller (for debugging only)
.TP
\fB\-\-dp\-hdmi\-info\fR
Show details about connected DP or HDMI Expansion Cards
.TP
\fB\-\-dp\-hdmi\-update\fR \fI<UPDATE_BIN>\fR
Update the DisplayPort or HDMI Expansion Card
.TP
\fB\-\-audio\-card\-info\fR
Show details about connected Audio Expansion Cards (Needs root privileges)
.TP
\fB\-\-privacy\fR
Show privacy switch statuses (camera and microphone)
.TP
\fB\-\-pd\-bin\fR \fI<PD_BIN>\fR
Parse versions from PD firmware binary file
.TP
\fB\-\-ec\-bin\fR \fI<EC_BIN>\fR
Parse versions from EC firmware binary file
.TP
\fB\-\-capsule\fR \fI<CAPSULE>\fR
Parse UEFI Capsule information from binary file
.TP
\fB\-\-dump\fR \fI<DUMP>\fR
Dump extracted UX capsule bitmap image to a file
.TP
\fB\-\-h2o\-capsule\fR \fI<H2O_CAPSULE>\fR
Parse UEFI Capsule information from binary file
.TP
\fB\-\-dump\-ec\-flash\fR \fI<DUMP_EC_FLASH>\fR
Dump EC flash contents
.TP
\fB\-\-flash\-full\-ec\fR \fI<FLASH_FULL_EC>\fR
Flash full EC flash with new firmware from file \- may render your hardware unbootable!
.TP
\fB\-\-flash\-ec\fR \fI<FLASH_EC>\fR
Flash EC (RO+RW) with new firmware from file \- may render your hardware unbootable!
.TP
\fB\-\-flash\-ro\-ec\fR \fI<FLASH_RO_EC>\fR
Flash EC with new RO firmware from file \- may render your hardware unbootable!
.TP
\fB\-\-flash\-rw\-ec\fR \fI<FLASH_RW_EC>\fR
Flash EC with new RW firmware from file
.TP
\fB\-\-intrusion\fR
Show status of intrusion switch
.TP
\fB\-\-inputdeck\fR
Show status of the input modules
.TP
\fB\-\-inputdeck\-mode\fR \fI<INPUTDECK_MODE>\fR
Set input deck power mode [possible values: auto, off, on, reset] (Laptop 12, 13, 16)
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
auto
.IP \(bu 2
off
.IP \(bu 2
on
.IP \(bu 2
reset
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-expansion\-bay\fR
Show status of the expansion bay (Laptop 16 only)
.TP
\fB\-\-charge\-limit\fR [\fI<CHARGE_LIMIT>\fR]
Get or set max charge limit
.TP
\fB\-\-charge\-current\-limit\fR \fI<CHARGE_CURRENT_LIMIT>...\fR
Set max charge current limit
.TP
\fB\-\-charge\-rate\-limit\fR \fI<CHARGE_RATE_LIMIT>...\fR
Set max charge current limit
.TP
\fB\-\-get\-gpio\fR [\fI<GET_GPIO>\fR]
Get GPIO value by name or all, if no name provided
.TP
\fB\-\-fp\-led\-level\fR [\fI<FP_LED_LEVEL>\fR]
Get or set fingerprint LED brightness level
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
high
.IP \(bu 2
medium
.IP \(bu 2
low
.IP \(bu 2
ultra\-low
.IP \(bu 2
auto
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-fp\-brightness\fR [\fI<FP_BRIGHTNESS>\fR]
Get or set fingerprint LED brightness percentage
.TP
\fB\-\-kblight\fR [\fI<KBLIGHT>\fR]
Set keyboard backlight percentage or get, if no value provided
.TP
\fB\-\-remap\-key\fR \fI<REMAP_KEY>...\fR
Remap a key by changing the scancode
.TP
\fB\-\-rgbkbd\fR \fI<START>\fR\fI \fR\fI<HEXCOLOR>...\fR
Set the color of <key> to <RGB>. Multiple colors for adjacent keys can be set at once. <key> <RGB> [<RGB> ...] Example: 0 0xFF000 0x00FF00 0x0000FF
.TP
\fB\-\-tablet\-mode\fR \fI<TABLET_MODE>\fR
Set tablet mode override
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
auto
.IP \(bu 2
tablet
.IP \(bu 2
laptop
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-touchscreen\-enable\fR \fI<TOUCHSCREEN_ENABLE>\fR
Enable/disable touchscreen
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
true
.IP \(bu 2
false
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-haptic\-intensity\fR \fI<INTENSITY>\fR
Set touchpad haptic feedback intensity
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
0
.IP \(bu 2
25
.IP \(bu 2
50
.IP \(bu 2
75
.IP \(bu 2
100
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-click\-force\fR \fI<CLICK_FORCE>\fR
Set touchpad click force / sensitivity
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
low
.IP \(bu 2
medium
.IP \(bu 2
high
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-stylus\-battery\fR
Check stylus battery level (USI 2.0 stylus only)
.TP
\fB\-\-console\fR \fI<CONSOLE>\fR
Get EC console, choose whether recent or to follow the output
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
recent
.IP \(bu 2
follow
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-reboot\-ec\fR \fI<REBOOT_EC>\fR
Control EC RO/RW jump
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
reboot
.IP \(bu 2
jump\-ro
.IP \(bu 2
jump\-rw
.IP \(bu 2
cancel\-jump
.IP \(bu 2
disable\-jump
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-ec\-hib\-delay\fR [\fI<EC_HIB_DELAY>\fR]
Get or set EC hibernate delay (S5 to G3)
.TP
\fB\-\-sysinfo\fR
Show system info (reset flags, current image, locked state)
.TP
\fB\-\-uptimeinfo\fR

.TP
\fB\-\-s0ix\-counter\fR

.TP
\fB\-\-hello\fR
Check basic communication with EC
.TP
\fB\-\-hash\fR \fI<HASH>\fR
Hash a file of arbitrary data
.TP
\fB\-\-driver\fR \fI<DRIVER>\fR
Select which driver is used. By default portio is used
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
portio
.IP \(bu 2
cros\-ec
.IP \(bu 2
windows
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-pd\-addrs\fR \fI<PD_ADDRS>...\fR
Specify I2C addresses of the PD chips (Advanced)
.TP
\fB\-\-pd\-ports\fR \fI<PD_PORTS>...\fR
Specify I2C ports of the PD chips (Advanced)
.TP
\fB\-t\fR, \fB\-\-test\fR
Run self\-test to check if interaction with EC is possible
.TP
\fB\-\-test\-retimer\fR
Run self\-test to check if interaction with retimers is possible
.TP
\fB\-\-boardid\fR
Print all board IDs
.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-force\fR
Force execution of an unsafe command \- may render your hardware unbootable!
.TP
\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
Simulate execution of a command (e.g. \-\-flash\-ec)
.TP
\fB\-\-flash\-gpu\-descriptor\-file\fR \fI<FLASH_GPU_DESCRIPTOR_FILE>\fR
File to write to the gpu EEPROM
.TP
\fB\-\-dump\-gpu\-descriptor\-file\fR \fI<DUMP_GPU_DESCRIPTOR_FILE>\fR
File to dump the gpu EEPROM to
.TP
\fB\-\-validate\-gpu\-descriptor\-file\fR \fI<VALIDATE_GPU_DESCRIPTOR_FILE>\fR
File to validate the gpu EEPROM against
.TP
\fB\-\-nvidia\fR
Show NVIDIA GPU information (Laptop 16 only)
.TP
\fB\-\-host\-command\fR \fI<HOST_COMMAND>...\fR
Send an EC host command. Args: <CMD_ID> <VERSION> [DATA...]
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.SH EXAMPLES
List all firmware versions:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
# framework_tool \-\-versions
.fi
.RE
.PP
Show battery and AC status:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
# framework_tool \-\-power
.fi
.RE
.PP
Get keyboard backlight level:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
# framework_tool \-\-kblight
.fi
.RE
.PP
Set keyboard backlight to 50%:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
# framework_tool \-\-kblight 50
.fi
.RE
.PP
Set battery charge limit to 80%:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
# framework_tool \-\-charge\-limit 80
.fi
.RE
.PP
Parse version from EC firmware file:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
$ framework_tool \-\-ec\-bin ec.bin
.fi
.RE
.PP
Flash EC RW firmware:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
# framework_tool \-\-flash\-rw\-ec ec_rw.bin
.fi
.RE
.PP
